Interface Iterator<T>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractUniversalIterator, ArrayIterator, CharacterIterator, FileHierarchyIterator, FilteredIterator, IteratorAdapter, JEnumerationAdapter, JIteratorAdapter, JoiningIterator, ListIterator, MappingIterator, MatchResultIterator, NodeListIterator, ReaderIterator
public interface Iterator<T>

The Gang of Four's favorite iterator interface. Abstracts the traversal of an aggregate structure from the underlying representation. Note that method names have been modified from those given by the Gang of Four but the behavior is the same. Use an iterator as follows: 

 Iterator<SomeType> iter = someMethod();
 for(iter.reset(); !iter.isDone(); iter.advance()) {
    // do something with iter.current()
 }

Author:
Miorel-Lucian Palii
